Description: An identifier for the set of data. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to a collection or institution.
Examples: The ScienceBase ID number of the dataset

Description: The nature or genre of the resource.
Examples: This will be Stream Habitat for all values

Description: The most recent date-time on which the combined dataset was changed.
Examples: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601:2004(E).

Description: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.
Examples: Example: BLM AIM, EPA NARS, USFS ARMEP

Description: A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used.
An identifier for the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.
An identifier for the collection or dataset from which the record was derived.
The name identifying the data set from which the record was derived.
The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record
